      • evaluatePointPosition

        public int evaluatePointPosition(Vector2D point)
        Returns an integer, describing whether a point is inside, on, or outside of the cell: 
         -1: point is outside the perimeter of the cell
  0: point is on the perimeter of the cell
  1: point is inside the perimeter of the cell
        Parameters:
        point - The point to check.
        Returns:
        -1 if the point is outside of the perimeter of the cell, 0 if point is on the perimeter of the cell and 1 if the point is inside of the cell
